In detection systems, the '''noise-equivalent target (NET)''' is the [[Radiant Intensity|intensity]] of a target measured by a system when the [[signal-to-noise ratio]] of the system is&nbsp;1.

[[Noise-equivalent temperature]] is an example for noise-equivalent target.

