'''Cusec''' is a measure of flow rate and is informal shorthand for "[[cubic feet per second|'''cu'''bic feet per '''sec'''ond]]"<ref name=Row/> (28.317 litres per second).<ref name=Row/> In the United States it is generally applied to water flow, particularly in rivers. Other informal synonyms are ''[[Cubic feet per second|cfs]]'' and ''second-feet''.
* 1 ft<sup>3</sup>s<sup>−1</sup> = 0.028316847m<sup>3</sup>s<sup>−1</sup>, 1 ft<sup>3</sup>s<sup>−1</sup> = 1 cusec * 1 ft<sup>3</sup>s<sup>−1</sup> = 28.316847 litre s<sup>−1</sup>, 1 cubic foot per minute = 1 cufm * 1 cusec = 1.699m<sup>3</sup>min<sup>−1</sup>, 1 cusec = 1699 litres min<sup>−1</sup> * 1 gallon per minute = 0.07577 litre s<sup>−1</sup>, 1 gallon per minute = 7.577x10-5m<sup>3</sup>s<sup>−1</sup> (These are UK not US gallons: 1 [[imperial gallon]] = 1.201 US gallons)
==See also== * [[Cumec]], for cubic meter per second
